{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"name":"ir","display_name":"R","language":"R"},"language_info":{"name":"R","codemirror_mode":"r","pygments_lexer":"r","mimetype":"text/x-r-source","file_extension":".r","version":"4.4.0"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"none","dataSources":[{"sourceType":"competition","sourceId":100890,"databundleVersionId":12488425},{"sourceType":"datasetVersion","sourceId":12059156,"datasetId":3845418,"databundleVersionId":12583465},{"sourceType":"datasetVersion","sourceId":12079194,"datasetId":9,"databundleVersionId":12605762},{"sourceType":"datasetVersion","sourceId":12066649,"datasetId":3240808,"databundleVersionId":12591830}],"dockerImageVersionId":30749,"isInternetEnabled":true,"language":"r","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":false}},"nbformat_minor":4,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# How long does it take to make progress in Kaggle?\n\nI am one of the first users of Kaggle - more precisely, user number 650.\n\nAfter registering about 15 years ago, life happened and I never managed to participate much. Only recently, this year, I was able to complete my registration and join some competitions.\n\nAm I the slowest Kaggle participant ever? To verify this, let's compute how long does it take for users to achieve a new rank, and see how the distribution looks like (spoiler alert: I really am!)\n\nUnfortunately we are only able to compute the time it has taken for a user to get to their current rank since they registered. It is not possible to know how long it took them to go between one rank and the others, because the data is not saved.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"suppressPackageStartupMessages({\n  # Since I am old style, let's use R\n  library(tidyverse)  \n  library(patchwork) \n  library(lubridate)\n  library(collapse)\n  # set_collapse(mask = \"manip\")  # Use collapse instead of tidyverse for group_by/summarise\n  options(repr.plot.width = 16, repr.plot.height = 12)\n})\n","metadata":{"_uuid":"8f2839f25d086af736a60e9eeb907d3b93b6e0e5","_cell_guid":"b1076dfc-b9ad-4769-8c92-a6c4dae69d19","trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-06-06T14:42:33.95744Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-06-06T14:42:33.960341Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-06-06T14:42:35.813966Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-06-06T14:42:35.811993Z"},"_kg_hide-input":true,"_kg_hide-output":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## TLDR;\n\nYes, I really am the person who took the longest to achieve Expert rank. I'm significantly slower, with a p-value of 0.01318.\n\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Config\n\nYou can customize these variables to create a report for your own rank and tier. Just change the values and rerun the notebook. You can find the user id in the Users table.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"my_user_id = 650 # Your user Id, taken from the Users table. Used for plotting\nyour_tier <- \"Expert\"  \n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-06-06T14:42:35.816855Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-06-06T14:42:35.850181Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-06-06T14:42:35.866055Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-06-06T14:42:35.864234Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### Reading Data and parsing dates","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"users = read_csv(\"/kaggle/input/meta-kaggle/Users.csv\") %>% \n    filter(PerformanceTier != 0) %>% # Novice users are not relevant for this notebook\n    filter(PerformanceTier != 5) %>% # Exclude Kaggle Team members\n    mutate(RegisterDate = mdy(RegisterDate)) \n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-06-06T14:42:35.868985Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-06-06T14:42:35.870508Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-06-06T14:45:30.56171Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-06-06T14:45:30.559683Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"users %>% dim \nusers %>% head ","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-06-06T14:45:30.566267Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-06-06T14:45:30.568223Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-06-06T14:45:30.632216Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-06-06T14:45:30.629819Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Note: PerformanceTier 5 corresponds to Kaggle Team Members. See https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/kaggle/meta-kaggle/discussion/211164\nusers %>% count(PerformanceTier) ","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-06-06T14:45:30.636508Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-06-06T14:45:30.638658Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-06-06T14:45:30.704304Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-06-06T14:45:30.701478Z"},"_kg_hide-input":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"user_achievements = read_csv(\"/kaggle/input/meta-kaggle/UserAchievements.csv\")  %>% \n    filter(Tier >0 ) %>% # Novice tier is not relevant\n    mutate(TierAchievementDate = mdy(TierAchievementDate))\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-06-06T14:45:30.709547Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-06-06T14:45:30.711774Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-06-06T14:49:11.280288Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-06-06T14:49:11.277915Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"user_achievements %>% dim\nuser_achievements %>% head","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-06-06T14:49:11.285485Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-06-06T14:49:11.287309Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-06-06T14:49:11.343433Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-06-06T14:49:11.341584Z"},"_kg_hide-input":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"user_achievements %>% count(Tier) ","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-06-06T14:49:11.346262Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-06-06T14:49:11.347837Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-06-06T14:49:11.41546Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-06-06T14:49:11.413305Z"},"_kg_hide-input":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"user_achievements %>% tail","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-06-06T14:49:11.41835Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-06-06T14:49:11.41992Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-06-06T14:49:11.461102Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-06-06T14:49:11.458814Z"},"_kg_hide-input":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"This is how data looks like for a specific user (me). I'm an Expert in Scripts and Discussion, and Contributor in Competitions and Datasets.\n\nUnfortunately, we only have one data point per user/category. This means we cannot track the full progression, e.g. from rank 0 to rank 1, then rank 1 to rank 2, because the data is not tracked. ","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# This is me\nusers %>% filter(Id == my_user_id)\nuser_achievements %>% filter(UserId==my_user_id)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-06-06T14:49:11.465275Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-06-06T14:49:11.467175Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-06-06T14:49:11.547585Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-06-06T14:49:11.545642Z"},"_kg_hide-input":false},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Calculating Time to Current rank","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"user_achievements = user_achievements %>%\n    left_join(\n        users %>% select(UserId=Id, RegisterDate, PerformanceTier)#, \n        #by = join_by(Id)\n    ) %>% \n    mutate(achievement_delay = abs(TierAchievementDate - RegisterDate )) ","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-06-06T14:49:11.550512Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-06-06T14:49:11.552219Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-06-06T14:49:12.049759Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-06-06T14:49:12.047724Z"},"_kg_hide-input":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"user_achievements %>% filter(UserId==my_user_id)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-06-06T14:49:12.053359Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-06-06T14:49:12.05517Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-06-06T14:49:12.128092Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-06-06T14:49:12.124307Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"tier_labels <- c(\n  \"0\" = \"Novice\",\n  \"1\" = \"Contributor\",\n  \"2\" = \"Expert\",\n  \"3\" = \"Master\",\n  \"4\" = \"Grandmaster\",\n  \"5\" = \"Kaggle Team\"\n)\n\nuser_achievements = user_achievements %>%\n  mutate(\n    PerformanceTierFactor = factor(\n      as.character(PerformanceTier),\n      levels = names(tier_labels),\n      labels = tier_labels\n    ),\n    TierFactor = factor(\n      as.character(Tier),\n      levels = names(tier_labels),\n      labels = tier_labels\n    ),\n    AchievementType = as.factor(AchievementType)\n  )","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-06-06T14:49:12.133189Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-06-06T14:49:12.136007Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-06-06T14:49:14.205658Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-06-06T14:49:14.203437Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"user_achievements %>% head","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-06-06T14:49:14.210189Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-06-06T14:49:14.212175Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-06-06T14:49:14.261683Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-06-06T14:49:14.259651Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"time_to_current_rank = user_achievements %>%\n    #filter(!is.na(achievement_delay)) %>%\n    filter(Tier == PerformanceTier) %>%\n    fgroup_by(UserId, PerformanceTierFactor) %>%\n    fsummarise(time_to_current_tier = min(achievement_delay)) %>%\n    ungroup #%>% \n    #arrange(UserID)\ntime_to_current_rank %>% head","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-06-06T14:49:14.264577Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-06-06T14:49:14.266209Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-06-06T14:49:27.564031Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-06-06T14:49:27.561796Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"my_tier <- time_to_current_rank %>%\n  filter(UserId == my_user_id) %>%\n  select(PerformanceTierFactor, time_to_current_tier)\nmy_tier","metadata":{"trusted":true,"_kg_hide-input":true,"_kg_hide-output":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-06-06T14:49:27.567433Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-06-06T14:49:27.569181Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-06-06T14:49:27.601825Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-06-06T14:49:27.599552Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"time_to_current_rank %>% head","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-06-06T14:49:27.604916Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-06-06T14:49:27.60647Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-06-06T14:49:27.632977Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-06-06T14:49:27.631184Z"},"_kg_hide-input":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## How long does it take for people to get to their Kaggle Rank?\n\nThe plot below shows how much time it takes for people to achieve their top rank.\n\nI'm the red line - an outlier at the end of the tail.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"library(ggplot2)\nlibrary(dplyr)\nlibrary(patchwork)  # or use cowplot::plot_grid()\n\n# Step 1: compute 75th percentiles per tier\nq3_limits <- time_to_current_rank %>%\n  group_by(PerformanceTierFactor) %>%\n  summarise(q3 = quantile(time_to_current_tier, 0.75, na.rm = TRUE))\n\n# Step 2: plot full distribution\np_full <- time_to_current_rank %>%\n  ggplot(aes(time_to_current_tier)) +\n  geom_histogram(binwidth = 100, fill = \"steelblue\", alpha = 0.7) +\n  geom_vline(\n    data = my_tier,\n    aes(xintercept = time_to_current_tier),\n    color = \"red\", linetype = \"dashed\", size = 1\n  ) +\n  facet_wrap(~PerformanceTierFactor, scales = \"free_y\") +\n  labs(title = \"Days taken to reach best Kaggle Rank (red line: Me)\",\n       x = \"Days\", y = \"Number of Users\") +\n  theme_minimal()\n\n# Step 3: zoomed-in plot by filtering to Q3\np_zoom <- time_to_current_rank %>%\n  inner_join(q3_limits, by = \"PerformanceTierFactor\") %>%\n  filter(time_to_current_tier <= q3) %>%\n  ggplot(aes(time_to_current_tier)) +\n  geom_histogram(binwidth = 50, fill = \"steelblue\", alpha = 0.7) +\n  facet_wrap(~PerformanceTierFactor, scales = \"free_y\") +\n  labs(title = \"Days taken to reach best Kaggle Rank - Zoomed In (Up to 75th Percentile)\",\n       x = \"Days\", y = \"Number of Users\") +\n  theme_minimal()\n\n# Step 4: plot\np_full\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-06-06T14:49:27.63632Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-06-06T14:49:27.637785Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-06-06T14:49:29.072297Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-06-06T14:49:29.070168Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":" p_zoom ","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-06-06T14:49:29.075105Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-06-06T14:49:29.076518Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-06-06T14:49:29.889234Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-06-06T14:49:29.887103Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"my_delay <- time_to_current_rank %>%\n  filter(UserId == my_user_id) %>%\n  pull(time_to_current_tier)%>% as.numeric\n\nexpert_distribution <- time_to_current_rank %>%\n  #filter(!is.na(PerformanceTier)) %>%\n  filter(PerformanceTierFactor == \"Expert\") %>%\n  pull(time_to_current_tier) %>% as.numeric\n\nyour_percentile <- mean(expert_distribution <= my_delay, na.rm = TRUE)\n\ncat(\"You are slower than\", round(100 * your_percentile, 2), \"% of Experts.\\n\")\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-06-06T14:49:29.8921Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-06-06T14:49:29.893635Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-06-06T14:49:29.929449Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-06-06T14:49:29.92767Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### Summary Stats\n\nThe table below shows a summary of how much does it take people to achieve their best rank in Kaggle. \n\n- Using median values, it takes 346 days to become Contributor; 577 to become Expert; 971 to become Master; and 1326 to become Granmaster.\n- Somebody managed to achieve Grandmaster rank in 25 days. Impressive!","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"time_summary <- time_to_current_rank %>%\n  ungroup() %>%\n  filter(!is.na(PerformanceTierFactor), !is.na(time_to_current_tier)) %>%\n  mutate(\n    days_to_current_tier = as.numeric(time_to_current_tier)\n  ) %>%\n  group_by(PerformanceTierFactor) %>%\n  summarise(\n    n_users = n(),\n    min_days = min(days_to_current_tier, na.rm = TRUE),\n    p25 = quantile(days_to_current_tier, 0.25, na.rm = TRUE),\n    median_days = median(days_to_current_tier, na.rm = TRUE),\n    p75 = quantile(days_to_current_tier, 0.75, na.rm = TRUE),\n    second_slowest_days = sort(days_to_current_tier, decreasing = TRUE)[2],\n    max_days = max(days_to_current_tier, na.rm = TRUE),\n    mean_days = mean(days_to_current_tier, na.rm = TRUE),\n    sd_days = sd(days_to_current_tier, na.rm = TRUE),\n  )\ntime_summary","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-06-06T14:49:29.932142Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-06-06T14:49:29.933576Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-06-06T14:49:30.053393Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-06-06T14:49:30.051563Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### What is my p-value?\n\nAm I significantly slower than most? To compute this, let's compute the log of the days taken to reach expert rank (so it is a pseudo-normal distribution) and compute the pvalue.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# ### Evaluate best Data transformation\n# x <- as.numeric(time_to_current_rank$time_to_current_tier)\n# # Log1p (safe for zeros)\n# x_log <- log1p(x)\n\n# # Box-Cox (only positive)\n# boxcox_obj <- boxcox(x)\n# x_boxcox <- boxcox_obj$x.t\n\n# # Yeo-Johnson (handles zero and negative)\n# yj_obj <- yeojohnson(x)\n# x_yj <- yj_obj$x.t\n\n# # Quantile normalization to normal\n# qt_obj <- orderNorm(x)\n# x_qt <- qt_obj$x.t\n# plot_density <- function(data, label) {\n#   ggplot(data.frame(x = data), aes(x)) +\n#     geom_histogram(aes(y = ..density..), bins = 40, fill = \"steelblue\", alpha = 0.7) +\n#     geom_density(color = \"red\", size = 1) +\n#     ggtitle(paste(\"Distribution:\", label))\n# }\n\n# plot_density(x, \"Original\") +\n# plot_density(x_log, \"Log1p\") +\n# plot_density(x_boxcox, \"Box-Cox\") +\n# plot_density(x_yj, \"Yeo-Johnson\") +\n# plot_density(x_qt, \"Quantile Transform\")\n# shapiro.test(x_log)\n# shapiro.test(x_boxcox)\n# shapiro.test(x_yj)\n# shapiro.test(x_qt)\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2025-06-06T14:49:30.05636Z","iopub.execute_input":"2025-06-06T14:49:30.057923Z","iopub.status.idle":"2025-06-06T14:49:30.108619Z","shell.execute_reply":"2025-06-06T14:49:30.091919Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"log_data <- time_to_current_rank %>%\n  filter(PerformanceTierFactor == your_tier) %>%\n  mutate(\n    delay_days = as.numeric(time_to_current_tier),\n    log_delay = log1p(delay_days)  # log1p handles 0 safely\n  )\nmy_log_delay <- log_data %>%\n  filter(UserId == 650) %>%\n  pull(log_delay)\nlog_mean <- mean(log_data$log_delay, na.rm = TRUE)\nlog_sd   <- sd(log_data$log_delay, na.rm = TRUE)\n\nz_score <- (my_log_delay - log_mean) / log_sd\np_value <- pnorm(z_score, lower.tail = FALSE)  # one-sided upper tail\n\ncat(\"Log-transformed Z-score:\", round(z_score, 2), \"\\n\")\ncat(\"Parametric one-sided p-value:\", signif(p_value, 4), \"\\n\")\n","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## How much does it take to reach a rank within every category?\n\nThere are four categories in Kaggle - Competitions, Datasets, Code, Discussion. The previous cells shows the stats for the highest of these four, for each user. In the plots below, we delve into every single cateogy","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"time_by_type_summary <- user_achievements %>%\n  filter(!is.na(PerformanceTierFactor), !is.na(achievement_delay)) %>%\n  mutate(\n    days_to_current_tier = as.numeric(achievement_delay)\n  ) %>%\n  group_by(AchievementType, PerformanceTierFactor) %>%\n  summarise(\n    n_users = n(),\n    min_days = min(days_to_current_tier, na.rm = TRUE),\n    p25 = quantile(days_to_current_tier, 0.25, na.rm = TRUE),\n    median_days = median(days_to_current_tier, na.rm = TRUE),\n    p75 = quantile(days_to_current_tier, 0.75, na.rm = TRUE),\n    second_slowest_days = sort(days_to_current_tier, decreasing = TRUE)[2],\n    max_days = max(days_to_current_tier, na.rm = TRUE),\n    mean_days = mean(days_to_current_tier, na.rm = TRUE),\n    sd_days = sd(days_to_current_tier, na.rm = TRUE),\n  )\ntime_by_type_summary","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"user_achievements %>% head","metadata":{"trusted":true,"_kg_hide-input":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"my_tier_by_type <- user_achievements %>%\n  filter(UserId == my_user_id) \nmy_tier\n# Step 2: plot full distribution\np_full <- user_achievements %>%\n  ggplot(aes(achievement_delay)) +\n  geom_histogram(binwidth = 100, fill = \"steelblue\", alpha = 0.7) +\n  geom_vline(\n    data = my_tier_by_type,\n    aes(xintercept = achievement_delay),\n    color = \"red\", linetype = \"dashed\", size = 1\n  ) +\n  facet_wrap(~PerformanceTierFactor+AchievementType, scales = \"free_y\") +\n  labs(title = \"Days taken to achieve each rank - split by Category. (Red line: Me)\",\n       x = \"Days\", y = \"Number of Users\") +\n  theme_minimal()\n\n\np_full","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null}]}